body:
### Describe the bug

This issue has been originally reported in Stack Trace: https://stackoverflow.com/questions/76790895/panacherepositoryresource-transaction-is-not-active

Having the following REST Data interface:

```java
@ResourceProperties(hal = true, paged = false, halCollectionName = "item-collections")
public interface CollectionsResource extends PanacheRepositoryResource<CollectionsRepository, Collection, String> {
    @Transactional
    @POST
    @Path("/name/{name}")
    default Collection addByName(@PathParam("name") String name) {
        Collection collection = new Collection();
        collection.id = name;
        collection.name = name;
        collection.persist();
        return collection;
    }
}
```

It fails with:
```
2023-07-31 08:12:56,638 ERROR [io.qua.ver.htt.run.QuarkusErrorHandler] (executor-thread-1) HTTP Request to /collections/name/mycollection failed, error id: 07a3c279-b23b-497c-b17b-69fc85e34489-1: org.jboss.resteasy.spi.UnhandledException: jakarta.persistence.TransactionRequiredException: Transaction is not active, consider adding @Transactional to your method to automatically activate one.
```

Note that internally the REST Data with Panache extension is auto-generating a resource XX_AutoGenerated that implements the above interface CollectionsResource.

### Expected behavior

The `@Transactional` annotation should work when using it on default methods and for auto-generated resources.



### Actual behavior

_No response_

### How to Reproduce?

_No response_

